org.apache.poi.hssf.record.chart

Class ChartRecord

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.poi.hssf.record.RecordBase
      • org.apache.poi.hssf.record.Record
        • org.apache.poi.hssf.record.StandardRecord
          • org.apache.poi.hssf.record.chart.ChartRecord
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Duplicatable, GenericRecord 

    public final class ChartRecord
extends StandardRecord
    CHART (0x1002)

    The chart record is used to define the location and size of a chart.

    Chart related records don't seem to be covered in either the OOO or the MS documentation. The book "Microsoft Excel 97 Developer's Kit" ISBN: (1-57231-498-2) seems to have an entire chapter (10) devoted to Chart records. One blog suggests that some documentation for these records is available in "MSDN Library, Feb 1998", but no later.

    (CHART（0x 1002）图表记录用于定义图表的位置和大小。OOO或MS文档中似乎都没有涵盖图表相关记录。《Microsoft Excel 97 Developer ' s Kit》一书ISBN：（1-57231-498-2）似乎有整整一章（10）专门讨论图表记录。一个博客建议，这些记录的一些文档可以在“NSO Library，Feb 1998”中找到，但以后不会出现。)

        public void serialize(LittleEndianOutput out)
        Description copied from class: StandardRecord
        Write the data content of this BIFF record. The 'ushort sid' and 'ushort size' header fields have already been written by the superclass.

        The number of bytes written must equal the record size reported by RecordBase.getRecordSize()} minus four ( record header consisting of a 'ushort sid' and 'ushort reclength' has already been written by their superclass).

        (写入此BIFF记录的数据内容。超类已经编写了“ushort sid”和“ushort size”标头字段。写入的字节数必须等于RecordBase报告的记录大小。getRecordSize（）}减四（由“ushort sid”和“ushort reclong”组成的记录头已由其超类写入）。)
